On Jun 15 2007 18:56, Vegard Nossum wrote:
> bool is_power_of_2(unsigned long n)
> {
>-	return (n != 0 && ((n & (n - 1)) == 0));
>+	return n * !(n & (n - 1));
> }
There is a third way which uses neither * nor &&, but []:
bool is_power_of_2(unsigned long n)
{
	static const bool yn[] = {
		[0] = false,
		[1 ... (8 * sizeof(n) - 1)] = true,
	};
	return yn[(n & (n - 1)) == 0];
}
	Jan
